HEADWORD: Sacro-
<hw>Sa"cro-</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>. <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A combining
form denoting <xex>connection with</xex>, or <xex>relation to</xex>,
<xex>the sacrum</xex>, as in <xex>sacro</xex>-coccygeal,
<xex>sacro</xex>-iliac, <xex>sacro</xex>sciatic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

